value.name: Mary & George
value.overview: In 17th century England, Mary Villiers molds her beautiful son, George, to seduce King James I, intending to gain riches and influence through outrageous schemes.

value.name: King George and Queen Mary: The Royals Who Rescued the Monarchy
value.original_name: King George and Queen Mary: The Royals Who Rescued the Monarchy
value.overview: King George and Queen Mary: The Royals Who Rescued the Monarchy. Documentary examining the couple who rescued the monarchy. King George V was an unlikely moderniser but his innovations were key. A two-part portrait of Elizabeth II's grandparents, King George V and Queen Mary, which examines the lasting legacy of the couple who rescued the monarchy from potential disaster, and whose influence persists to this day.
